        {
            "_id": "qOa3vmdDP9MrMZpX",
            "img": "systems/sf2e/icons/actions/TwoActions.webp",
            "name": "Devastation's Truth",
            "sort": 0,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The Devourer's temptation manifests an intrusive vision of destruction and doom, attempting to awe all who experience it with the power of the Devourer and the inevitability of death for them and all their loved ones. All uninitiated creatures in the worship chamber must attempt a @Check[will|dc:24] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and can immediately attempt to help an affected creature as a reaction (see Disable).</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[(2d8+9)[mental]] damage and is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Fascinated] until a creature revives them. The creature is then immune to Devastation's Truth for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes @Damage[(4d8+18)[mental]] damage, is fascinated until a creature revives them, and is @UUID[Compendium.sf2e.conditions.Item.Stupefied]{Stupefied 2} for 24 hours. The creature is then immune to Devastation's Truth for 24 hours.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "OGL",
                    "remaster": false,
                    "title": ""
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": null,
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "incapacitation"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        }
